MrBayes 3.2.7-dev (development version)

Using GNU autotools (Autoconf and Automake):

*   Make sure Autoconf 2.69 is installed.
*   Make sure Automake 1.15 is installed.

*   On some systems who uses metaauto for wrapping multiple versions of
    the GNU autotools:

    $ export AUTOCONF_VERSION=2.69
    $ export AUTOMAKE_VERSION=1.15

*   Run autoheader to create "config.h.in" from "configure.ac":

    $ autoheader

*   Run aclocal to create "aclocal.m4" from "configure.ac":

    $ aclocal

*   Run automake to create "Makefile.in" from "Makefile.am":

    $ automake --add-missing

*   Run autoconf to create "configure":

    $ autoconf

*   Run configure to create "Makefile":

    $ configure

*   Make the project:

    $ make
